flowRoot.flowPara: The index.html home page looks a bit plain. You can change how it looks with CSS!
From this... To this... Using CSS!
A CSS file contains the recipe for how the web page appears.
It's a separate file from the HTML file and it's linked to the HTML file like this:
Open the index.html file in your text editor and locate the link (its the fifth line down).
What this link is telling you is that the appearance of the page is controlled by a stylesheet named simple.css which is located in the css folder.
